sequenceDiagram
  participant Op as Operator (host)
  participant C as Channel domain
  participant HW as HV hardware

  Note over C: operating_mode = Normal

  loop every fresh ADC sample
    C->>C: consume_current(raw)
    C->>C: tick_current_protection()
  end

  C->>C: measured_current > current_limit_threshold
  C->>C: active_fault_cause |= CURRENT
  C->>HW: apply protection action (e.g. DisableImmediate)
  Note over C: state = FaultLatched

  C->>C: tick_recovery() runs every tick
  Note over C: operating_mode != Automatic -> return immediately.<br/>No auto-retry, no cooldown, ever.

  rect rgb(245, 245, 245)
    Note over Op,HW: Channel stays FaultLatched indefinitely<br/>until an operator acts.
  end

  Op->>C: Fault Command = Clear Active
  C->>C: is_safe_to_clear_active()?
  alt still unsafe (current still above safe band)
    C-->>Op: VC_ERR_UNSAFE_STATE
  else safe now
    C->>C: active_fault_cause = 0, state = DisabledSafe
    C-->>Op: VC_OK
    Op->>C: Output Action = Enable
    C->>HW: ramp up to configured_target_voltage
    Note over C: state = Ramping -> EnabledHolding
  end
